@USBLN We’ve had a great time chatting and seeing the responses today! Thanks @USBLN for highlighting the conversation about #disability in the workplace. #InForInclusion #USBLN2018
@USBLN A6.3 @USBLN can also be a great partner in this area and a great resource! #INforInclusion #USBLN2018
@USBLN A6.2 At CSX, we source talent through certain recruiting avenues specifically because they connect us to candidates with disabilities.  #INforInclusion

@USBLN A6.1 We use military recruiting platforms, which tend to return a higher percentage of candidates with disabilities, and we have an employee referral process that promotes #diversity in recruiting and hiring. #INforInclusion
@USBLN A5.5 Through training, we show managers how to drill down to identify the specific skill sets that enable someone to perform the job successfully.  #INforInclusion

@USBLN A5.4 We encourage hiring managers to focus on the actual job requirements and not assume that certain attributes are necessary simply because people who have performed the job in the past have had them.  #INforInclusion
@USBLN A5.3 We strongly encourage hiring managers to refresh their training even if they have completed the courses in the past.  #INforInclusion
@USBLN A5.2 We offer effective interviewing training, a course in #disability etiquette and have conducted unconscious bias seminars. #INforInclusion
@USBLN A5.1 CSX has several training courses that help our hiring managers to be more inclusive in the hiring process. #INforInclusion
@USBLN A4.6 Ensuring all employees have the same experience and feel involved beginning on day one is key to an inclusive environment. #INforInclusion
@USBLN A4.5 We work with our medical department to ensure we provide appropriate accommodations for all employees from the pre-hire phase through their entire CSX career. #INforInclusion
@USBLN A4.4 Another example is we provide sign language interpreters for the hearing impaired in our New Hire onboarding class. #INforInclusion

@USBLN A4.3 One example of how we practice inclusivity is our process for onboarding service animals.  We acclimate the service animal to our work environment, and familiarize the work groups to the animal. #INforInclusion
@USBLN A4.2 Once we’ve made a hiring decision, we focus on the effectiveness of the onboarding process and making necessary accommodations. #INforInclusion
@USBLN A4.1 One easy way to be more inclusive is simply to ask how the candidate feels about our interview process and ask how we can make it a comfortable and effective experience. #INforInclusion
@USBLN A3.2 It’s also important to be clear that resources are available and how to find them. We want to make sure people’s first experience with our company is a positive one. #INforInclusion
@USBLN A3.1 It’s important to make sure there is accessibility information available on the front end for candidates with disabilities. #INforInclusion
@USBLN A2.4 People with disabilities who find us to be an accommodating employer also tend to be long-term, committed employees. #INforInclusion

@USBLN A2.3 Employees with disabilities help us by making recommendations for how to make the workplace more accessible and inclusive, and very often those improvements — both physical and cultural — benefit all employees #INforInclusion
@USBLN A2.2 In general, people with different backgrounds and experiences increase our appreciation for different ways of getting work done and performing effectively. #INforInclusion
@USBLN A2.1 CSX is committed to being an inclusive company, and people with disabilities are an important part of diversity. #INforInclusion
@USBLN A1.4 Beyond that, we have found that using a broad range of sourcing avenues increases the diversity of the candidates we reach across all categories. #INforInclusion

@USBLN A1.3 In addition, military recruiting platforms tend to return a higher percentage of candidates with disabilities & we have an employee referral program that promotes diversity in recruiting and hiring. #INforInclusion
@USBLN A1.2 We also partner with local agencies and participate in disability symposiums and career fairs. #INforInclusion
@USBLN A1.1: At CSX, we choose certain recruiting avenues specifically because they connect us to candidates with disabilities. USBLN Going for the Gold is a great resource. #INforInclusion
